result.execSummary:
On one or more charges, the deferred prosecution or sentencing agreement(s) on this case were fulfilled, and the charge(s) were dismissed.

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

No crimes at level of p.c., Restitution $2500, AODA and comply, Obtain assessment for anger management or Domestic abuse treatment. No contact with victim.  Victim rights complied with.  State heard on victim input.  Atty Laufenberg agrees with plea agreement.  Atty Laufenberg gives resolution on case. Plea questionnaire and waiver or rights. Def. understands charge and penalties.  Ct 1 Substantial Battery, Bodily harm Domestic Abuse, no contest plea.  DRI Ct 2. Def. advised of constitutional rights & J.T. rights. Def. understand elements.  Atty Laufenberg is satisfied.  Court finds plea is freely & voluntarily given.  Factual basis set forth.  Atty Laufenberg agrees to factual basis left unchallenged.  Court finds factual basis, accept plea and finds def. Guilty to Substantial Battery, Bodily harm domestic abuse.  Court reads parts of complaint.  Atty Laufenberg gives defense. Court will approve Defer Judgment for 2 years  and will sign agreement.  If def complies with agreement case will be dismissed or if violates than will go into sentence.  Court will convert to $1,000 Signature bond and bond to be returned to defendant.
